      <section class="topic" id="cheatsheet-section">
        <div class="topic-head"><h2><span class="tagnum">📋</span> Printable Revision Cheat Sheet</h2></div>
        <p style="color:var(--text-dim); font-size:13.5px;">One line per concept — for the 10 minutes before you walk in.</p>
        <div class="cheatsheet">
          <table>
            <tr><th>Concept</th><th>One-line answer</th></tr>
            <tr><td>Interface vs Abstract</td><td>Interface: contract only, multiple allowed. Abstract: real code + state, single inheritance.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Trait</td><td>Reusable method block pasted into unrelated classes — behavior, not identity.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>PSR-4</td><td>Composer autoload standard mapping namespace prefix → folder path.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Service Container</td><td>Resolves class dependencies via reflection; bindings needed for interfaces.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>bind() vs singleton()</td><td>bind: new instance every resolve. singleton: one shared instance for app lifetime.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Facade</td><td>Static-looking call that forwards via __callStatic to a container-resolved object.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>register() vs boot()</td><td>register: only bindings. boot: setup that needs other providers already registered.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Gate vs Policy</td><td>Gate: closure, broad checks. Policy: class scoped to a specific model's actions.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>N+1 problem</td><td>1 query for parents + 1 per row for relations; fix with eager loading (with()).</td></tr>
            <tr><td>withCount/withAvg</td><td>Computes aggregates in SQL instead of pulling rows into PHP to aggregate.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Job idempotency</td><td>Running a queued job twice (due to retries) must produce the same end state.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Event vs direct call</td><td>Event/listener decouples side effects; caller doesn't know who's listening.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Repository pattern</td><td>Abstracts data access behind an interface — swap/fake implementation freely.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Service layer</td><td>Holds business/use-case logic; keeps controllers thin (HTTP concerns only).</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Sanctum</td><td>Lightweight token/cookie auth for SPAs and APIs.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>composer.lock</td><td>Pins exact resolved dependency versions for reproducible installs.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Feature vs Unit test</td><td>Feature: full HTTP request through the framework. Unit: single class in isolation.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>config:cache risk</td><td>Must be cleared/rebuilt after any .env change or stale values persist in prod.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>queue:restart</td><td>Required after deploy — long-running workers hold old code in memory otherwise.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Redis common uses</td><td>Cache, queues, rate limiting, session storage — beyond just key-value caching.</td></tr>
          </table>
        </div>
