const rapidFire = [
  ["What's the difference between == and === in PHP?", "== compares with type coercion (loose); === compares value and type with no coercion. Always prefer === to avoid surprises like '0' == false being true."],
  ["What is a magic method? Name three.", "Methods PHP calls automatically on certain triggers instead of being called explicitly: __construct (instantiation), __get/__set (accessing undefined properties), __call (calling undefined methods), __toString (casting an object to a string)."],
  ["What's the difference between require and require_once?", "require_once checks if the file was already included and skips it if so, preventing redeclaration errors; require always includes it, even if already loaded."],
  ["What is dependency injection, in one line?", "Supplying a class's dependencies from the outside (usually via constructor) instead of the class creating them itself internally."],
  ["What's the difference between public, protected, and private?", "public: accessible anywhere. protected: accessible within the class and subclasses. private: accessible only within the declaring class itself."],
  ["What does the 'final' keyword do on a class or method?", "Prevents the class from being extended, or the method from being overridden in a subclass."],
  ["What is method chaining and how is it implemented?", "Calling multiple methods in sequence on the same object (fluent interface) — implemented by having each method return $this."],
  ["What's the difference between artisan migrate and migrate:fresh?", "migrate runs pending migrations only; migrate:fresh drops all tables first, then re-runs every migration from scratch — destructive, never for production."],
  ["What is a Form Request in Laravel?", "A dedicated class for validation and authorization logic, injected into a controller method instead of validating inline, keeping controllers thin."],
  ["What does Eloquent's $fillable vs $guarded do?", "$fillable is an allowlist of mass-assignable fields; $guarded is a denylist. Both protect against mass-assignment vulnerabilities — use one, not both."],
  ["What is a database transaction, and how do you use one in Laravel?", "A set of operations that all succeed or all roll back together, wrapped with DB::transaction(fn () => { ... }) — critical for multi-step writes like a booking + payment record."],
  ["What's the difference between soft deletes and hard deletes?", "Soft delete (SoftDeletes trait) sets a deleted_at timestamp and excludes the row from normal queries without removing it; hard delete removes the row permanently."],
  ["What does php artisan tinker do?", "Opens an interactive REPL with the full application booted, letting you run Eloquent queries and test code live against real app state."],
  ["What is a Laravel Resource (API Resource)?", "A dedicated class that transforms a model (or collection) into a controlled, consistent JSON structure for API responses, decoupling the response shape from the raw database columns."],
  ["What's the difference between a Job and an Event?", "A Job represents one unit of async work meant to be processed, typically once. An Event represents 'something happened' and can trigger multiple independent Listeners."],
  ["How does Laravel's rate limiting middleware work?", "throttle:60,1 limits a client to 60 requests per 1 minute, tracked per IP/user via the cache, returning a 429 response once exceeded."],
  ["What is the difference between hasOne and belongsTo?", "Both describe a one-to-one relationship but from opposite sides — hasOne is on the table holding the 'parent' side, belongsTo is on the table holding the foreign key."],
  ["What does php artisan optimize do in older Laravel versions / what replaced it?", "It historically cached config/routes/views together; modern Laravel favors running config:cache, route:cache, and view:cache separately for more granular control."],
  ["What is method overloading in PHP, and does PHP support it natively?", "PHP doesn't support true method overloading (same name, different signatures) like Java/C#; __call and __callStatic magic methods can simulate similar dynamic dispatch behavior."],
  ["What's the difference between abstract methods and interface methods?", "Both declare a signature without implementation, but abstract methods live in a class that can also have real implemented methods and state; interfaces are pure contracts with no implementation at all."],
  ["What does array_map vs array_filter do?", "array_map transforms every element and returns an array of the same length; array_filter removes elements that don't pass a callback, returning a possibly-shorter array."],
  ["What is Laravel's Sanctum used for vs Passport?", "Sanctum: lightweight token/cookie auth for SPAs, mobile apps, simple APIs. Passport: full OAuth2 server implementation for more complex third-party API auth scenarios."],
  ["What is eager loading vs lazy loading in Eloquent?", "Eager loading (with()) fetches relations upfront in a batched query; lazy loading fetches a relation only when it's first accessed, which is what causes the N+1 problem if done in a loop."],
